{
  "texts": [
    "D. Crossbar-Wise QuantizationQuantization is a commonly used model compression technique that works by transforming the input to a lower-bit representation through a discretization process.",
    "Recently, QLoRA (Quantized Low-Rank Adaptation) has been proposed for transformer fine-tuning.",
    "QLoRA extends the principle of LoRA by quantizing the pre-trained model [5].",
    "It employs two precision types, a low-precision storage format for the weights and a high-precision format for computing.",
    "Eq. 4 shows the QLoRA computation kernel."
  ]
}